The paper focuses on modeling influence propagation in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS subfields such as social computing (cs.SOC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a new model for influence propagation that is scalable and efficient, which suggests that it may be relevant to the subfield of scalable systems (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD).
